do it officially. You know...

53
00:03:06,352 --> 00:03:08,513
Oh. Oh um...

54
00:03:08,588 --> 00:03:10,453
Yeah. Oh um... Here.

55
00:03:18,398 --> 00:03:23,335
Sophie, would you do me the honor
of marrying me?

56
00:03:23,403 --> 00:03:27,863
Sophie Bremmer
was still a hopeless romantic.

57
00:03:27,941 --> 00:03:33,880
On one condition. Tomorrow
we trade this in for a ring of my own.

58
00:03:33,947 --> 00:03:37,041
And I want a bigger diamond
than Dolores got.

59
00:03:38,484 --> 00:03:41,976
But she was no longer naive.

60
00:04:26,866 --> 00:04:30,267
Marriage is a simple concept.

61
00:04:30,336 --> 00:04:34,204
Basically, it's a contract
betwen two people

62
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:38,005
that binds them together for life

63
00:04:38,077 --> 00:04:41,740
in the hopes that
they can live happily ever after.

64
00:04:42,982 --> 00:04:47,476
Sadly, some contracts...
are made to be broken.

65
00:04:47,553 --> 00:04:50,716
- I didn't mess with your birth control.
- Really?

66
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:52,587
Really.

67
00:04:56,162 --> 00:04:59,791
Look. It's been pulled apart
and put back together.

68
00:04:59,866 --> 00:05:03,927
- It's probably a manufacturing defect.
- You can still see the glue marks.

69
00:05:04,003 --> 00:05:06,233
I'm telling you, I didn't do it.

70
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:08,103
Don't insult me, Carlos.

71
00:05:08,174 --> 00:05:10,734
You've been whining about
wanting a baby for months.

72
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:12,175
Who else would it have been?

73
00:05:12,245 --> 00:05:13,507
I don't...

74
00:05:15,114 --> 00:05:17,446
- Oh, no.
- What?

75
00:05:17,517 --> 00:05:19,644
- Mama.
- Oh, please.

76
00:05:19,719 --> 00:05:24,486
It's possible. You buy that stuff
in bulk, six months at a time, right?

77
00:05:24,557 --> 00:05:25,854
Yeah. So?

78
00:05:25,925 --> 00:05:29,554
Before the accident, I told her
how much I wanted to have a child.

79
00:05:29,629 --> 00:05:32,063
She said that she would take care of it.

80
00:05:32,131 --> 00:05:35,328
I just thought that
she would talk to you.

81
00:05:35,401 --> 00:05:37,869
Baby, I am so sorry.

82
00:05:44,410 --> 00:05:47,277
That bitch.

83
00:05:47,347 --> 00:05:49,178
I can't believe her.

84
00:05:49,248 --> 00:05:52,706
I loved her
but even I had issues sometimes.

85
00:05:52,785 --> 00:05:54,514
She could be very controlling.

86
00:05:54,587 --> 00:05:57,522
Reaching out from the grave
to screw with me.

87
00:05:59,392 --> 00:06:01,587
God, she's good.

88
00:06:03,663 --> 00:06:05,494
Where are you going?

89
